{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":812,"text":"So I started working"},{"time":2449,"text":"with refugees because I wanted"},{"time":4333,"text":"to make a difference,"},{"time":6673,"text":"and making a difference starts"},{"time":8080,"text":"with telling their stories."},{"time":10436,"text":"So when I meet refugees,"},{"time":11926,"text":"I always ask them questions."},{"time":14726,"text":"Who bombed your house?"},{"time":17044,"text":"Who killed your son?"},{"time":19697,"text":"Did the rest of your family make it out alive?"},{"time":23741,"text":"How are you coping"},{"time":25727,"text":"in your life in exile?"},{"time":28258,"text":"But there's one question that always seems to me"},{"time":31261,"text":"to be most revealing, and that is:"},{"time":33725,"text":"What did you take?"},{"time":35907,"text":"What was that most important thing"},{"time":38157,"text":"that you had to take with you"},{"time":40229,"text":"when the bombs were exploding in your town,"},{"time":43635,"text":"and the armed gangs were approaching your house?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":48060,"text":"A Syrian refugee boy I know"},{"time":50665,"text":"told me that he didn't hesitate"},{"time":53355,"text":"when his life was in imminent danger."},{"time":57145,"text":"He took his high school diploma,"},{"time":60126,"text":"and later he told me why."},{"time":62055,"text":"He said, \"I took my high school diploma"},{"time":65263,"text":"because my life depended on it.\""},{"time":68469,"text":"And he would risk his life to get that diploma."},{"time":71698,"text":"On his way to school, he would dodge snipers."},{"time":75380,"text":"His classroom sometimes shook"},{"time":77895,"text":"with the sound of bombs and shelling,"},{"time":81129,"text":"and his mother told me,"},{"time":83936,"text":"\"Every day, I would say to him every morning,"},{"time":87005,"text":"'Honey, please don't go to school.'\""},{"time":89931,"text":"And when he insisted, she said,"},{"time":93390,"text":"\"I would hug him as if it were for the last time.\""},{"time":97362,"text":"But he said to his mother,"},{"time":99392,"text":"\"We're all afraid,"},{"time":101237,"text":"but our determination to graduate"},{"time":104128,"text":"is stronger than our fear.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":107462,"text":"But one day, the family got terrible news."},{"time":110798,"text":"Hany's aunt, his uncle and his cousin"},{"time":113532,"text":"were murdered in their homes for refusing"},{"time":116221,"text":"to leave their house."},{"time":117215,"text":"Their throats were slit."},{"time":120080,"text":"It was time to flee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122711,"text":"They left that day, right away, in their car,"},{"time":125725,"text":"Hany hidden in the back because they were facing"},{"time":127586,"text":"checkpoints of menacing soldiers."},{"time":131496,"text":"And they would cross the border into Lebanon,"},{"time":135208,"text":"where they would find peace."},{"time":137904,"text":"But they would begin a life of grueling hardship"},{"time":141586,"text":"and monotony."},{"time":144590,"text":"They had no choice but to build a shack"},{"time":147289,"text":"on the side of a muddy field,"},{"time":148622,"text":"and this is Hany's brother Ashraf,"},{"time":150940,"text":"who plays outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152678,"text":"And that day, they joined"},{"time":155100,"text":"the biggest population of refugees in the world,"},{"time":160304,"text":"in a country, Lebanon, that is tiny."},{"time":163330,"text":"It only has four million citizens,"},{"time":165981,"text":"and there are one million Syrian refugees living there."},{"time":169551,"text":"There's not a town, a city or a village"},{"time":173645,"text":"that is not host to Syrian refugees."},{"time":178392,"text":"This is generosity and humanity"},{"time":181587,"text":"that is remarkable."},{"time":185961,"text":"Think about it this way, proportionately."},{"time":188955,"text":"It would be as if"},{"time":190711,"text":"the entire population of Germany,"},{"time":193702,"text":"80 million people,"},{"time":195567,"text":"would flee to the United States in just three years."},{"time":200957,"text":"Half of the entire population of Syria"},{"time":204118,"text":"is now uprooted,"},{"time":206548,"text":"most of them inside the country."},{"time":208303,"text":"Six and a half million people"},{"time":210598,"text":"have fled for their lives."},{"time":213320,"text":"Over and well over three million people"},{"time":216210,"text":"have crossed the borders"},{"time":217932,"text":"and have found sanctuary\nin the neighboring countries,"},{"time":221475,"text":"and only a small proportion, as you see,"},{"time":224400,"text":"have moved on to Europe."},{"time":228534,"text":"What I find most worrying"},{"time":231205,"text":"is that half of all Syrian refugees are children."},{"time":235131,"text":"I took this picture of this little girl."},{"time":237369,"text":"It was just two hours after she had arrived"},{"time":240294,"text":"after a long trek from Syria into Jordan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244636,"text":"And most troubling of all"},{"time":248061,"text":"is that only 20 percent of \nSyrian refugee children"},{"time":251802,"text":"are in school in Lebanon."},{"time":255277,"text":"And yet, Syrian refugee children,"},{"time":258210,"text":"all refugee children tell us"},{"time":260508,"text":"education is the most important thing in their lives."},{"time":265574,"text":"Why? Because it allows them to think of their future"},{"time":269755,"text":"rather than the nightmare of their past."},{"time":273150,"text":"It allows them to think of hope rather than hatred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278784,"text":"I'm reminded of a recent visit I took"},{"time":280813,"text":"to a Syrian refugee camp in northern Iraq,"},{"time":284390,"text":"and I met this girl,"},{"time":286202,"text":"and I thought, \"She's beautiful,\""},{"time":287979,"text":"and I went up to her and asked her,"},{"time":289686,"text":"\"Can I take your picture?\""},{"time":291634,"text":"And she said yes,"},{"time":293333,"text":"but she refused to smile."},{"time":296370,"text":"I think she couldn't,"},{"time":299419,"text":"because I think she must realize that she represents"},{"time":302925,"text":"a lost generation of Syrian refugee children,"},{"time":307369,"text":"a generation isolated and frustrated."},{"time":311950,"text":"And yet, look at what they fled:"},{"time":315496,"text":"utter destruction,"},{"time":317335,"text":"buildings, industries, schools, roads, homes."},{"time":322914,"text":"Hany's home was also destroyed."},{"time":325593,"text":"This will need to be rebuilt"},{"time":328806,"text":"by architects, by engineers, by electricians."},{"time":333637,"text":"Communities will need teachers and lawyers"},{"time":337284,"text":"and politicians interested in reconciliation"},{"time":341525,"text":"and not revenge."},{"time":344169,"text":"Shouldn't this be rebuilt"},{"time":345924,"text":"by the people with the largest stake,"},{"time":349015,"text":"the societies in exile, the refugees?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354880,"text":"Refugees have a lot of time"},{"time":357634,"text":"to prepare for their return."},{"time":359880,"text":"You might imagine that being a refugee"},{"time":362595,"text":"is just a temporary state."},{"time":365103,"text":"Well far from it."},{"time":368044,"text":"With wars going on and on,"},{"time":371560,"text":"the average time a refugee will spend in exile"},{"time":375362,"text":"is 17 years."},{"time":378827,"text":"Hany was into his second year in limbo"},{"time":382415,"text":"when I went to visit him recently,"},{"time":384789,"text":"and we conducted our entire conversation in English,"},{"time":388546,"text":"which he confessed to me he learned"},{"time":390435,"text":"from reading all of Dan Brown's novels"},{"time":394089,"text":"and from listening to American rap."},{"time":398444,"text":"We also spent some nice moments of laughter"},{"time":401189,"text":"and fun with his beloved brother Ashraf."},{"time":405823,"text":"But I'll never forget what he told me"},{"time":407444,"text":"when we ended our conversation that day."},{"time":410868,"text":"He said to me,"},{"time":413281,"text":"\"If I am not a student, I am nothing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":418810,"text":"Hany is one of 50 million people"},{"time":422527,"text":"uprooted in this world today."},{"time":426105,"text":"Never since World War II"},{"time":428884,"text":"have so many people been forcibly displaced."},{"time":434151,"text":"So while we're making sweeping progress"},{"time":436780,"text":"in human health,"},{"time":438881,"text":"in technology, in education and design,"},{"time":443875,"text":"we are doing dangerously little"},{"time":447238,"text":"to help the victims"},{"time":450546,"text":"and we are doing far too little"},{"time":453245,"text":"to stop and prevent"},{"time":455281,"text":"the wars that are driving them from their homes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458690,"text":"And there are more and more victims."},{"time":463133,"text":"Every day, on average,"},{"time":466267,"text":"by the end of this day,"},{"time":468449,"text":"32,000 people will be forcibly displaced"},{"time":472297,"text":"from their homes —"},{"time":474332,"text":"32,000 people."},{"time":479271,"text":"They flee across borders like this one."},{"time":483020,"text":"We captured this on the Syrian border to Jordan,"},{"time":486715,"text":"and this is a typical day."},{"time":493588,"text":"Or they flee on unseaworthy and overcrowded boats,"},{"time":498492,"text":"risking their lives in this case"},{"time":500292,"text":"just to reach safety in Europe."},{"time":502923,"text":"This Syrian young man"},{"time":504638,"text":"survived one of these boats that capsized —"},{"time":507424,"text":"most of the people drowned —"},{"time":509047,"text":"and he told us,"},{"time":511262,"text":"\"Syrians are just looking for a quiet place"},{"time":515421,"text":"where nobody hurts you,"},{"time":518290,"text":"where nobody humiliates you,"},{"time":520832,"text":"and where nobody kills you.\""},{"time":523543,"text":"Well, I think that should be the minimum."},{"time":526761,"text":"How about a place of healing,"},{"time":529888,"text":"of learning,"},{"time":531766,"text":"and even opportunity?"},{"time":536832,"text":"Americans and Europeans"},{"time":538856,"text":"have the impression that proportionally"},{"time":542107,"text":"huge numbers of refugees are coming"},{"time":544480,"text":"to their country,"},{"time":546500,"text":"but the reality is"},{"time":548642,"text":"that 86 percent, the vast majority of refugees,"},{"time":552287,"text":"are living in the developing world,"},{"time":554967,"text":"in countries struggling with their own insecurity,"},{"time":559520,"text":"with their own issues of helping their own populations"},{"time":563539,"text":"and poverty."},{"time":565662,"text":"So wealthy countries in the world should recognize"},{"time":568935,"text":"the humanity and the generosity of the countries"},{"time":572636,"text":"that are hosting so many refugees."},{"time":576754,"text":"And all countries should make sure that no one"},{"time":580386,"text":"fleeing war and persecution"},{"time":582939,"text":"arrives at a closed border."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586652,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589282,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594200,"text":"But there is something more that we can do"},{"time":596505,"text":"than just simply helping refugees survive."},{"time":600915,"text":"We can help them thrive."},{"time":604446,"text":"We should think of refugee camps and communities"},{"time":607506,"text":"as more than just temporary population centers"},{"time":611713,"text":"where people languish"},{"time":613873,"text":"waiting for the war to end."},{"time":616782,"text":"Rather, as centers of excellence,"},{"time":620511,"text":"where refugees can triumph over their trauma"},{"time":624459,"text":"and train for the day that they can go home"},{"time":627643,"text":"as agents of positive change"},{"time":630724,"text":"and social transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635122,"text":"It makes so much sense,"},{"time":637508,"text":"but I'm reminded of the terrible war in Somalia"},{"time":641817,"text":"that has been raging on for 22 years."},{"time":645741,"text":"And imagine living in this camp."},{"time":648250,"text":"I visited this camp."},{"time":649823,"text":"It's in Djibouti, neighboring Somalia,"},{"time":651700,"text":"and it was so remote"},{"time":654244,"text":"that we had to take a helicopter to fly there."},{"time":656685,"text":"It was dusty and it was terribly hot."},{"time":660131,"text":"And we went to visit a school"},{"time":662425,"text":"and started talking to the children,"},{"time":664342,"text":"and then I saw this girl across the room"},{"time":666936,"text":"who looked to me to be the same age"},{"time":668785,"text":"as my own daughter, and I went up and talked to her."},{"time":672066,"text":"And I asked her the questions"},{"time":673610,"text":"that grown-ups ask kids,"},{"time":675789,"text":"like, \"What is your favorite subject?\""},{"time":677712,"text":"and, \"What do you want to be when you grow up?\""},{"time":680367,"text":"And this is when her face turned blank,"},{"time":683664,"text":"and she said to me,"},{"time":685714,"text":"\"I have no future."},{"time":688185,"text":"My schooling days are over.\""},{"time":691162,"text":"And I thought, there must be some misunderstanding,"},{"time":692810,"text":"so I turned to my colleague"},{"time":695119,"text":"and she confirmed to me"},{"time":697217,"text":"there is no funding for secondary education"},{"time":699910,"text":"in this camp."},{"time":702180,"text":"And how I wished at that moment"},{"time":703649,"text":"that I could say to her,"},{"time":705967,"text":"\"We will build you a school.\""},{"time":708372,"text":"And I also thought, what a waste."},{"time":712546,"text":"She should be and she is"},{"time":715594,"text":"the future of Somalia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719925,"text":"A boy named Jacob Atem"},{"time":723131,"text":"had a different chance, but not before he experienced"},{"time":726326,"text":"terribly tragedy."},{"time":728418,"text":"He watched — this is in Sudan —"},{"time":730882,"text":"as his village — he was only seven years old —"},{"time":733176,"text":"burned to the ground, and he learned"},{"time":735558,"text":"that his mother and his father"},{"time":737397,"text":"and his entire family"},{"time":739386,"text":"were killed that day."},{"time":741250,"text":"Only his cousin survived, and the two of them"},{"time":743040,"text":"walked for seven months —"},{"time":745320,"text":"this is boys like him —"},{"time":747170,"text":"chased and pursued by wild\nanimals and armed gangs,"},{"time":750378,"text":"and they finally made it to refugee camps"},{"time":752738,"text":"where they found safety,"},{"time":754271,"text":"and he would spend the next seven years"},{"time":756394,"text":"in Kenya in a refugee camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759581,"text":"But his life changed"},{"time":762109,"text":"when he got the chance to be resettled"},{"time":764212,"text":"to the United States,"},{"time":766417,"text":"and he found love in a foster family"},{"time":769113,"text":"and he was able to go to school,"},{"time":771701,"text":"and he wanted me to share with you"},{"time":773995,"text":"this proud moment"},{"time":775563,"text":"when he graduated from university."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777868,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783829,"text":"I spoke to him on Skype the other day,"},{"time":786243,"text":"and he was in his new university in Florida"},{"time":791237,"text":"pursuing his Ph.D. in public health,"},{"time":794236,"text":"and he proudly told me how he was able to raise"},{"time":797306,"text":"enough funds from the American public"},{"time":799990,"text":"to establish a health clinic back in his village"},{"time":804575,"text":"back home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807655,"text":"So I want to take you back to Hany."},{"time":810939,"text":"When I told him I was going to have the chance"},{"time":813160,"text":"to speak to you here on the TED stage,"},{"time":815877,"text":"he allowed me to read you a poem"},{"time":818172,"text":"that he sent in an email to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821532,"text":"He wrote:"},{"time":825270,"text":"\"I miss myself,"},{"time":827830,"text":"my friends,"},{"time":830335,"text":"times of reading novels or writing poems,"},{"time":834590,"text":"birds and tea in the morning."},{"time":839515,"text":"My room, my books, myself,"},{"time":844464,"text":"and everything that was making me smile."},{"time":850122,"text":"Oh, oh, I had so many dreams"},{"time":854250,"text":"that were about to be realized.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":859323,"text":"So here is my point:"},{"time":861551,"text":"Not investing in refugees"},{"time":863597,"text":"is a huge missed opportunity."},{"time":869241,"text":"Leave them abandoned,"},{"time":871092,"text":"and they risk exploitation and abuse,"},{"time":876439,"text":"and leave them unskilled and uneducated,"},{"time":879712,"text":"and delay by years the return"},{"time":882265,"text":"to peace and prosperity in their countries."},{"time":888115,"text":"I believe how we treat the uprooted"},{"time":891399,"text":"will shape the future of our world."},{"time":895972,"text":"The victims of war can hold the keys"},{"time":898926,"text":"to lasting peace,"},{"time":901447,"text":"and it's the refugees"},{"time":903256,"text":"who can stop the cycle of violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906923,"text":"Hany is at a tipping point."},{"time":909944,"text":"We would love to help him go to university"},{"time":912209,"text":"and to become an engineer,"},{"time":915269,"text":"but our funds are prioritized for the basics in life:"},{"time":919116,"text":"tents and blankets and mattresses and kitchen sets,"},{"time":923163,"text":"food rations and a bit of medicine."},{"time":927519,"text":"University is a luxury."},{"time":930916,"text":"But leave him to languish in this muddy field,"},{"time":935253,"text":"and he will become a member"},{"time":937214,"text":"of a lost generation."},{"time":940636,"text":"Hany's story is a tragedy,"},{"time":945340,"text":"but it doesn't have to end that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949073,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951450,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}